==English==
{{wikipedia|sovereignty}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|soverain|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|VL.|en}} root *''superānus'' (cf. Italian ''[[sovrano]]'', Spanish ''[[soberano]]'') from Latin {{term|super||above|lang=la}}. Plus the Latinate English suffix {{term|-ity|-ty|lang=en}}. Spelling influenced by folk-etymology association with reign.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈsɒv.ɹən.ti/|/ˈsɒv.ɹɪn.ti}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"sQv.r\@n.ti/|/"sQv.rIn.ti/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|sovereignties}}

# {{context|of a nation|lang=en}} The state of making laws and controlling resources without the coercion of other nations.
# {{context|of a ruler|lang=en}} Supreme authority over all things.
# {{context|of a person|lang=en}} The liberty to decide one's thoughts and actions.

